Etymology[edit]

From ex- +‎ sūcus (“juice, moisture”)

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ekˈsuː.koː/, [ɛkˈsuː.koː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ekˈsu.ko/, [ɛkˈsuː.kɔ]

Verb[edit]

exsūcō (present infinitive exsūcāre, perfect active exsūcāvī, supine exsūcātum); first conjugation

  1. I juice (remove juice from)
  2. I dry
